sec.p:
The ITS sequences of 212 individuals (38 populations) of 
   E. henryi were aligned with a total of length of 767 bp, exhibiting 10 nucleotide substitutions (ITS-1: 4; ITS-2: 6; 
   Table S6). Together, these 10 polymorphic sites identified nine ITS haplotypes (‘ribotypes’, R1–9; 
   Table S6). Of those, five ribotypes were specific to the Southern cpDNA lineage (R2–6) and three to the Northern cpDNA lineage (R7–9; 
   Fig. 2A). These lineage-specific ribotypes formed separate 
   tcs clades, except for the shared ribotype R1 (
   Fig. 2B).
